nment and international relations requires deeper understanding than textbook definitions provide.","why_cuet_level":"Involves evaluation of assertions against historical contexts of foreign policy.","distractor_rationale":{"A":"This option correctly links India's non-alignment with its diplomatic strategy during the Cold War.","B":"This option fails to recognize that both statements are indeed connected in their implications.","C":"This option misrepresents the historical context of India's independence from superpower influences.","D":"This option incorrectly states that the assertion is false."}},{"q":"Consider the following statements about India's international relations: Statement I: India has played a significant role in UN peacekeeping missions. Statement II: India's participation in these missions has always been universally praised without exceptions. Statement III: The role of regional conflicts often influences India's approach to global peacekeeping efforts. Which evaluation best captures the situation?","o":["I and II only","I and III only","II and III only","I, II and III"],"a":"B","question_type":"statement_based","concept_id":"political_science::india_s_external_relations","trap_option":"A","strong_distractors":["C","D"],"why_not_textbook":"The evaluation requires analysis beyond mere participation in peacekeeping; it considers global perceptions as well.","why_cuet_level":"Encourages critical thinking about India's motivations and challenges in peacekeeping roles.","distractor_rationale":{"A":"This option incorrectly assumes that all participation is viewed positively without exception.","B":"This option accurately captures the complexity of India's peacekeeping role amidst various criticisms.","C":"This option overlooks the nuances associated with international responses to India's missions.","D":"This option misrepresents the relationship between regional conflicts and peacekeeping effectiveness."}}]}
